Maggi seasoning, a brand of Nestle Nigeria, has donated food items such as rice, vegetable oil, spaghetti and Maggi seasoning to 100,000 consumers. Category Manager for Culinary at Nestlé, Mrs Nwando Ajene, said it was for the eid celebration in Kano. According to her, other things done by Maggi include donations to 160 charitable organisations and mosques, as well as door-to-door visits to 1,250 homes to share healthy food items. “Ramadan is a special season for renewed dedication to the values of service and sharing goodness; values which Maggi also firmly represents. Looking back on the past year, 2021 brings a fresh appreciation of the joy and privilege of coming together.